ethersrv-linux: ethersrv-linux (server for EtherDFS)
ethersrv-linux:
ethersrv-linux: EtherDFS is an 'installable filesystem' TSR for MS-DOS. It maps a
ethersrv-linux: drive from a remote computer (typically Linux-based) to a local drive
ethersrv-linux: letter, using raw ethernet frames to communicate.
ethersrv-linux:
ethersrv-linux: ethersrv-linux is an implementation of EtherSRV for Linux. It allows
ethersrv-linux: a Linux computer to share its drive over Ethernet with multiple MS-DOS
ethersrv-linux: clients running EtherDFS.
